# Data Analytics / Data Engineering Interview Prep

Author: Nivethasry Malliga Nagarajan

## Overview

This repository contains SQL, Python, Machine Learning, and data pipeline examples that reflect real-world data analytics and data engineering scenarios.

It demonstrates my experience in building scalable data pipelines, performing data analysis, developing machine learning models, and enabling business insights through visualization.

---

## Skills Covered

### SQL
- Joins (Inner, Left, Right)
- CTEs (Common Table Expressions)
- Window Functions (ROW_NUMBER, RANK)
- Aggregations (SUM, COUNT, AVG)
- Deduplication and latest record logic
- Query optimization concepts

### Python
- Data cleaning using Pandas
- Handling missing values
- Removing duplicates
- Data aggregation and grouping
- Data validation and automation

### Machine Learning
- Classification and regression models (Logistic Regression, Random Forest, SVM)
- Feature engineering and data preprocessing
- Model evaluation (Accuracy, Precision, Recall, F1-score)
- NLP basics using NLTK (text processing, sentiment analysis)
- Integration of ML models into data pipelines

### Data Engineering Concepts
- ETL / ELT pipelines
- Data staging and transformation
- Batch and streaming processing (Kafka)
- Data quality validation and reconciliation
- Data warehousing concepts

### Data Visualization & BI
- Building dashboards using Tableau
- Creating interactive reports with filters and parameters
- Data storytelling and business insights
- Supporting self-service analytics

